<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Antenna with 41 segments; first antennal segment 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide and 2.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as second segment, third segment length 2.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
its maximum width; frons strongly rugose, more or less reticulate-rugose medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1 head, dorsal view 2 head, frontal view 3 head, lateral view 4 pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707212" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">2</figureCitation>
); three anterior coronal teeth large and lobe-shaped, both posterior ones smaller and wider; vertex with 3 strongly curved carinae anteriorly, followed by slightly reticulate-rugose medially and transverse rugae almost reaching occipital carina; temple slightly bulging, smooth and shiny (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1 head, dorsal view 2 head, frontal view 3 head, lateral view 4 pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707212" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">1</figureCitation>
), except for some fine punctures laterally; occipital carina distinct, strongly developed up to near level of ventral 0.5 of eye and not connected to hypostomal carina; hypostomal carina large, with several rugae and punctures (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1 head, dorsal view 2 head, frontal view 3 head, lateral view 4 pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707212" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Neck relatively slender and anteriorly shallowly concave (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1 head, dorsal view 2 head, frontal view 3 head, lateral view 4 pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707212" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">4</figureCitation>
), with several weak carinae anteriorly and three interrupted but rather strong carinae, below the middle of the pronotum postero-dorsally. Pronotal fold distinct and with area in front of fold largely smooth and shiny; middle part of pronotum moderately transversely carinate, without lateral groove; middle part of pronotum weakly differentiated from posterior part (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1 head, dorsal view 2 head, frontal view 3 head, lateral view 4 pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707212" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">4</figureCitation>
), and latero-posteriorly rather weakly convex; posterior part of pronotum generally with rather sparse setosity, propleuron coriaceous; prosternum densely foveolate and setose; convex part of mesopleuron strongly foveolate and with dense whitish setosity (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 5 - 7. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 5 mesosoma, dorsal view 6 mesosoma, lateral view 7 wings." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures5-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707213" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">6</figureCitation>
); mesosternum largely smooth (except some fine punctures); scutellum smooth and shiny except some foveolae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 5 - 7. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 5 mesosoma, dorsal view 6 mesosoma, lateral view 7 wings." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures5-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707213" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">5</figureCitation>
); propodeum dorsally almost glabrous (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 5 - 7. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 5 mesosoma, dorsal view 6 mesosoma, lateral view 7 wings." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures5-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707213" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">5</figureCitation>
), completely with large, circular foveolae, most foveolae well separated by relatively large interspaces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Wings</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Fore wing: wing membrane subhyaline (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 5–7" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 5 - 7. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 5 mesosoma, dorsal view 6 mesosoma, lateral view 7 wings." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures5-7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707213" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">7</figureCitation>
), and surface evenly bristly; vein 1-M moderately curved, 5.2-5.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as vein 1-SR and 1.2-1.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
vein m-cu; vein 2-SR 0.95-1.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as vein r; vein r ends 0.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of pterostigma behind level of apex of pterostigma; vein 1-SR 0.6-0.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as parastigmal vein; vein 3-CU1 distinct and curved apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Legs</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Hind coxa strong, annular, largely transversely striate, with long whitish setosity (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–11" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 8 - 11. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 8 hind coxa, lateral view 9 hind femur, lateral view 10 hind tibia, lateral view 11 hind tarsi, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures8-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707214" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">8</figureCitation>
); hind femur robust, largely smooth and shiny with scattered punctures (more densely developed basally; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 8–11" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 8 - 11. Megischus baogong Ge &amp; Tan, sp. nov. Holotype ♀ 8 hind coxa, lateral view 9 hind femur, lateral view 10 hind tibia, lateral view 11 hind tarsi, lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.85373.figures8-11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707214" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">9</figureCitation>
), hind femur ventrally with two large teeth and four minute teeth in between and one tooth behind large posterior tooth; hind tibia slender, moderately curved basally (Fig. 
